'North West England' is one of nine official regions of England at the first
level of NUTS for statistical purposes. The region comprises five ceremonial
counties of England â Cheshire, Cumbria, Greater Manchester, Lancashire and
Merseyside. The North West had a population of 7,052,000 in 2011. It is the third most populated region after
Greater London and the South East.
